<div class="viewalloc-help">
	<h2>Accounts and Usage Help</h2>
	
	<p>
		The Allocations/Usage application lists your current projects and
		allocation for those projects.  Below is an explanation of the data:
	</p>
	
	<fieldset>
		<legend>Project Title</legend>
		The title of this particular project.
	</fieldset>
	
	<fieldset>
		<legend>Charge Number</legend>
		The charge number for this particular project.
	</fieldset>
	
	<fieldset>
		<legend>Project PI?</legend>
		Whether or not you are the PI on this project.
	</fieldset>
	
	<fieldset>
		<legend>Grant Number</legend>
		The grant number for this particular project.
	</fieldset>
	
	<fieldset>
		<legend>Start Date</legend>
		The start date for this project.
	</fieldset>
	
	<fieldset>
		<legend>End Date</legend>
		The end date for this project.
	</fieldset>
	
	<fieldset>
		<legend>Resource</legend>
		The resource for which this allocation exists.  The 'teragrid'
		resource is comprised of the IA-64 machines at ANL, NCSA, and SDSC. 
		The 'teragrid_roaming' resource includes most TeraGrid resources.  All
		other resources are listed individually and follow the pattern
		<em>resource_name</em>.<em>site</em>.teragrid.
	</fieldset>
	
	<fieldset>
		<legend>Project Allocation</legend>
		The first number in the ratio is your remaining allocation.  The
		second number in the ratio is your total allocation.  The blue/gray
		bar is a graphical representation of these numbers and allows you to
		quickly glance and see how much allocation you have remaining for your
		projects.  It is also possible that you may be overdrawn, in which
		case <span class="stress">OVERDRAWN</span> will be displayed in place
		of the blue/gray bar.
	</fieldset>
	
	<fieldset>
		<legend>My Usage</legend>
		Your remaining allocation for this particular project.
	</fieldset>
	
	<fieldset>
		<legend>Alloc. Type</legend>
		The type of allocation.  This can have the values: <em>new, renewal,
		transfer</em>
	</fieldset>
</div>